Mexico has decided to close its borderto imports of fresh fruit from San Diego and Orange Counties inCalifornia, the U.S. Agriculture Department's officer in MexicoCity said in a field report.    The report, dated October 14, said the border closingbecame effective September 25 and also includes the surrounding70-mile area of the two counties.    While the ban applies specifically to Orange County fruitsthat are hosts of the Mediterranean fruit fly and San DiegoCounty fruits that are hosts of the Oriental fruit fly, theMexican Government will stop all fresh fruit shipments from thecounties until proof of non-infestation is provided, the reportsaid. Reuter&#3;